Dunno why this was removed, I didn't/don't have a problem with manaburn crits<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well there is some debate over this, some claim to have critted with it after the change, i don't have it so i can't tell.  If it truly doesn't crit anymore, it is probably a consequence of the dot-like effect it puts on the mob now.  I don't think damage focus effects it anymore either...<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4) Inability to obtain Sunstrike, GSS, EER as well as other less desirable but useful high-end spells<br>
People get Sunstrike and EER, it may be hard for the very casual player but it is possible even if frustrating. GSS is the only one I dont see becoming commonplace for 6 months or more. THO drops EER and hes not all that anymore.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Sunstrike has better availability than the other 2, no doubt, but on Veeshan i've never seen a copy drop (have gone to the single group spots, and occasionally kill the velious dragons that drop it) and i've only seen 2 copies for sale, 1 for 50K, and one for 100K.  The average casual player doesn't have that kind of plat.  EER...  atm, i don't think truly casual players can get it, it drops off a reasonable amount of mobs, but you need a decent mid tier guild to kill them, and i've never seem EER up for sale.  GSS...  lol.  I can't imagine that ever becoming commonplace.  If SS isn't common yet, i doubt any of the 3 ever will be.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>5) Relative availability of comparable Druid nukes (Moonfire) and Mage nukes (FoT)<br>
Its all about the ratio, 95%+ of mages are conj spec'd and the FoT is a bolt...miss one and your ratio/efficency goes right out the window. I can speak to the druid one.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
It is more than the ratio, it's also about the crit.  Crits are the only thing that reminds people of our damage.  Without GSS, a mage with FoT can outcrit a wizard of similiar level.  That has an effect on our general groupability and on people's perceptions.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>7) Decline in usefulness of Evacs in PoP due to graveyards<br>
